266
00:22:56,661 --> 00:23:00,388
A shy confidence, a soft small coat

267
00:23:01,206 --> 00:23:04,934
Folding bag side
pocket, close and near

268
00:23:05,752 --> 00:23:09,480
Keeps the small courage clear

269
00:23:10,298 --> 00:23:14,026
You tuck the note
where light won’t see

270
00:23:14,844 --> 00:23:18,572
And the song moves on with you and me

271
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:37,111
Cold line of breath on glass

272
00:23:37,940 --> 00:23:41,717
Warm line of day as it passes

273
00:23:42,546 --> 00:23:46,324
You draw one line and
then the fog appears

274
00:23:47,153 --> 00:23:50,930
A quiet shape between
your hands and ears

275
00:23:51,759 --> 00:23:55,536
Outside lights drift,
then soften fast

276
00:23:56,366 --> 00:24:00,143
Inside this room they
can feel the last

277
00:24:00,972 --> 00:24:04,749
Not every thing needs to be clear

278
00:24:05,579 --> 00:24:09,356
Some things get bright
when they are near

279
00:24:10,185 --> 00:24:13,962
A little pause, a little tune

280
00:24:14,791 --> 00:24:18,569
A little room for the small moon

281
00:24:19,398 --> 00:24:23,175
Window glass fog in the aisle

282
00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:27,782
Warm and cool in gentle style

283
00:24:28,611 --> 00:24:32,388
A breath-line fades,
then stays somehow

284
00:24:33,217 --> 00:24:36,995
Where we stand and learn to slow down

285
00:24:37,824 --> 00:24:41,601
The aisle keeps its
gentle spine tonight

286
00:24:42,430 --> 00:24:46,207
You wipe one line and leave it white

287
00:24:47,037 --> 00:24:50,814
No rush to prove it had a name

288
00:24:51,643 --> 00:24:55,420
Only a soft light and a softer flame

289
00:24:56,250 --> 00:25:00,027
Let the line clear by itself

290
00:25:00,856 --> 00:25:04,633
No need to force a map on ourselves

291
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:09,240
You look away, then look back slow

292
00:25:10,069 --> 00:25:13,846
The moment becomes what we can hold

293
00:25:14,675 --> 00:25:18,453
Window glass fog in the aisle

294
00:25:19,282 --> 00:25:23,059
Warm and cool in gentle style

295
00:25:23,888 --> 00:25:27,665
A breath-line fades,
then stays somehow

296
00:25:28,495 --> 00:25:32,272
Where we stand and learn to slow down

297
00:25:33,101 --> 00:25:36,878
The line clears, but
the light remains

298
00:25:37,708 --> 00:25:41,485
A soft room, a soft lane

299
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:02,840
Cart at the corner, lamp on low

300
00:26:05,362 --> 00:26:09,762
One warm circle on the floor

301
00:26:12,283 --> 00:26:16,683
The cart is packed and nearly still

302
00:26:19,205 --> 00:26:23,605
You slide the lamp
toward the window sill

303
00:26:26,126 --> 00:26:30,526
A little pool of gold on the aisle

304
00:26:33,048 --> 00:26:37,448
A small, certain way to tie the night

305
00:26:39,969 --> 00:26:44,369
No big finish, no bright chase

306
00:26:46,891 --> 00:26:51,291
Just a steady shape, a little grace

307
00:26:53,812 --> 00:26:58,212
I don't need a phrase
that proves it all

308
00:27:00,734 --> 00:27:05,134
I just keep the light
when voices call

309
00:27:07,655 --> 00:27:12,055
Cart-side table lamp, late and low

310
00:27:14,577 --> 00:27:18,977
Keeps the room from going cold

311
00:27:21,498 --> 00:27:25,898
We stay with the same calm line

312
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:32,820
And I feel this
moment still feel fine

313
00:27:35,342 --> 00:27:39,742
You hold one edge of the
tote, then set it down

314
00:27:42,263 --> 00:27:46,663
The lamp hums soft above the town

315
00:27:49,185 --> 00:27:53,585
Outside the street goes soft and thin

316
00:27:56,106 --> 00:28:00,506
Inside, the song slows
and lets us begin

317
00:28:03,028 --> 00:28:07,428
If this was just a long afternoon

318
00:28:09,949 --> 00:28:14,349
Then this calm note is the proof

319
00:28:16,871 --> 00:28:21,271
That a shared pause
can hold two minds

320
00:28:23,792 --> 00:28:28,192
Without a speech or a binding sign

321
00:28:30,714 --> 00:28:35,114
Cart-side table lamp, late and low

322
00:28:37,635 --> 00:28:42,035
Keeps the room from going cold

323
00:28:44,557 --> 00:28:48,957
A warm glow stays through the aisle

324
00:28:51,478 --> 00:28:55,878
Long after the line
in the day goes mild

325
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:19,800
Last store light on the table

326
00:29:25,534 --> 00:29:29,934
Door at the edge, still able

327
00:29:35,668 --> 00:29:40,068
The close bell hums once, then twice

328
00:29:45,802 --> 00:29:50,202
A slow light turns
warm and quiet twice

329
00:29:55,935 --> 00:30:00,335
You set your bag near
the edge of the tray

330
00:30:06,069 --> 00:30:10,469
I nod, and the room
starts to fade away

331
00:30:16,203 --> 00:30:20,603
No final answer, no final line

332
00:30:26,337 --> 00:30:30,737
Only this soft little night in time

333
00:30:36,471 --> 00:30:40,871
A place we shared, then set down

334
00:30:46,605 --> 00:30:51,005
A gentle close, not upside-down

335
00:30:56,738 --> 00:31:01,138
Last bookstore hour, soft and clear

336
00:31:06,872 --> 00:31:11,272
Keeps the hope a little near

337
00:31:17,006 --> 00:31:21,406
Not a finish, only a turn

338
00:31:27,140 --> 00:31:31,540
We keep this little light to burn

339
00:31:37,274 --> 00:31:41,674
Shadows climb, then touch the floor

340
00:31:47,408 --> 00:31:51,808
Your hand points down
the darkened door

341
00:31:57,542 --> 00:32:01,942
We leave the bookish air behind

342
00:32:07,675 --> 00:32:12,075
But not the calm it taught us to find

343
00:32:17,809 --> 00:32:22,209
If this stays open a little more

344
00:32:27,943 --> 00:32:32,343
We'll meet the day at the back door

345
00:32:38,077 --> 00:32:42,477
If this stays closed
for now it's fine

346
00:32:48,211 --> 00:32:52,611
The good part stays,
and the song stays mine

347
00:32:58,345 --> 00:33:02,745
Last bookstore hour, soft and clear

348
00:33:08,478 --> 00:33:12,878
Keeps the hope a little near

349
00:33:18,612 --> 00:33:23,012
Paper breath, lamp light, slow track

350
00:33:28,746 --> 00:33:33,146
The hour lets go, then comes back
